description.narrative:
-	Case fatality rate (CFR) during malaria and diarrhoeal disease outbreaks is maintained below 1%;
-	At least 60% of health facilities in affected regions provide epidemic prone disease surveillance information and timely weekly reports on the health situation shared with partners;
-	At least 100% of the management team and 80% of heads of health facilities in all affected districts are trained on utilization of IT tools, integrated disease surveillance and outbreak control measures management of malaria, water-borne diseases and other epidemics;
-	Supervision and monitoring of 36 targeted health facilities are carried out in the seven targeted districts by management teams at all levels.
-	At least, two health cluster coordination meetings have been organized at field and national levels during the project period.
